{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XRgDuC5kKHEQ241hjwzhGW","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile the comprehensive report.\n\n## Summary\n\nI've found all code related to the \"runs\" URL/endpoint. Here's the complete breakdown:\n\n### 1. HTTP Route Registration\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 139-158)**\n\nTwo main routes are registered:\n- `GET /runs` → `h.handleRunsList` (HTML handler)\n- `GET /api/runs` → `h.handleAPIRuns` (JSON API handler)\n\nBoth routes support the same query parameter filtering.\n\n### 2. HTML Route Handler\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 248-294)**\n\n`handleRunsList()` function:\n- Extracts `project` query parameter: `projectFilter := r.URL.Query().Get(\"project\")` (line 249)\n- If `projectFilter` is provided, filters runs by project directory\n- Otherwise, returns all runs\n- Passes `ProjectFilter` to template for display\n\n### 3. JSON API Handler\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 447-472)**\n\n`handleAPIRuns()` function:\n- Identical filtering logic as HTML handler\n- Extracts `project` query parameter: `projectFilter := r.URL.Query().Get(\"project\")` (line 448)\n- Returns JSON array of runs, optionally filtered by project\n\n### 4. Client Code Constructing URLs\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` (lines 48-106)**\n\nThree references to the runs endpoint with project filtering:\n- Line 55: `window.location.href = '/runs?project=' + encodeURIComponent(dir);` (HTML page)\n- Line 65: `url += '?project=' + encodeURIComponent(currentProject);` (API call)\n- Periodic polling fetches updated runs list every 3 seconds\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/projects.html` (line 27)**\n\nLink to filtered runs:\n- `<a href=\"/runs?project={{.Dir}}\" class=\"btn btn-secondary\">View Runs</a>`\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` (line 8)**\n\nLink to filtered runs from project detail page:\n- `<a href=\"/runs?project={{.Dir}}\" class=\"btn btn-secondary btn-sm\" style=\"margin-left:0.5rem\">View all runs</a>`\n\n### 5. Test Coverage\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_test.go` (lines 270-336)**\n\nTests verify both handlers:\n- `TestRunsList_ProjectFilter()` (lines 270-294): Tests HTML handler with and without filter\n- `TestAPIRuns_ProjectFilter()` (lines 309-336): Tests JSON API with and without filter\n- Both tests use `?project=/home/user/alpha` pattern\n\n### 6. Summary of URL Patterns\n\n| Endpoint | Route Pattern | Query Parameter | Handler | Response |\n|----------|---------------|-----------------|---------|----------|\n| Runs List (HTML) | `GET /runs` | `?project=<dir>` | `handleRunsList` | HTML page |\n| Runs API | `GET /api/runs` | `?project=<dir>` | `handleAPIRuns` | JSON array |\n\nBoth endpoints use the same query parameter name (`project`) which accepts a full project directory path (e.g., `/home/user/alpha`) and filters the runs list accordingly."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ad0b63251f6ce905d (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 53514\ntool_uses: 17\nduration_ms: 20909</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2ca48579-25a2-4d0a-bd77-fa02a187fbcd","uuid":"c16088e6-9811-44f2-b6ab-226dcf537913","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find all code related to the \"runs\" URL/endpoint, especially where it's registered as a route and where it's called with a \"project\" query parameter. Look for:\n1. HTTP route registration (e.g., mux.HandleFunc, router patterns)\n2. Any handler that serves runs filtered by project\n3. Client code that constructs URLs like \"runs?project=...\"\n4. Any web/UI templates that reference runs URLs\n\nSearch thoroughly across the entire codebase.","agentId":"ad0b63251f6ce905d","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile the comprehensive report.\n\n## Summary\n\nI've found all code related to the \"runs\" URL/endpoint. Here's the complete breakdown:\n\n### 1. HTTP Route Registration\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 139-158)**\n\nTwo main routes are registered:\n- `GET /runs` → `h.handleRunsList` (HTML handler)\n- `GET /api/runs` → `h.handleAPIRuns` (JSON API handler)\n\nBoth routes support the same query parameter filtering.\n\n### 2. HTML Route Handler\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 248-294)**\n\n`handleRunsList()` function:\n- Extracts `project` query parameter: `projectFilter := r.URL.Query().Get(\"project\")` (line 249)\n- If `projectFilter` is provided, filters runs by project directory\n- Otherwise, returns all runs\n- Passes `ProjectFilter` to template for display\n\n### 3. JSON API Handler\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 447-472)**\n\n`handleAPIRuns()` function:\n- Identical filtering logic as HTML handler\n- Extracts `project` query parameter: `projectFilter := r.URL.Query().Get(\"project\")` (line 448)\n- Returns JSON array of runs, optionally filtered by project\n\n### 4. Client Code Constructing URLs\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` (lines 48-106)**\n\nThree references to the runs endpoint with project filtering:\n- Line 55: `window.location.href = '/runs?project=' + encodeURIComponent(dir);` (HTML page)\n- Line 65: `url += '?project=' + encodeURIComponent(currentProject);` (API call)\n- Periodic polling fetches updated runs list every 3 seconds\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/projects.html` (line 27)**\n\nLink to filtered runs:\n- `<a href=\"/runs?project={{.Dir}}\" class=\"btn btn-secondary\">View Runs</a>`\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` (line 8)**\n\nLink to filtered runs from project detail page:\n- `<a href=\"/runs?project={{.Dir}}\" class=\"btn btn-secondary btn-sm\" style=\"margin-left:0.5rem\">View all runs</a>`\n\n### 5. Test Coverage\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_test.go` (lines 270-336)**\n\nTests verify both handlers:\n- `TestRunsList_ProjectFilter()` (lines 270-294): Tests HTML handler with and without filter\n- `TestAPIRuns_ProjectFilter()` (lines 309-336): Tests JSON API with and without filter\n- Both tests use `?project=/home/user/alpha` pattern\n\n### 6. Summary of URL Patterns\n\n| Endpoint | Route Pattern | Query Parameter | Handler | Response |\n|----------|---------------|-----------------|---------|----------|\n| Runs List (HTML) | `GET /runs` | `?project=<dir>` | `handleRunsList` | HTML page |\n| Runs API | `GET /api/runs` | `?project=<dir>` | `handleAPIRuns` | JSON array |\n\nBoth endpoints use the same query parameter name (`project`) which accepts a full project directory path (e.g., `/home/user/alpha`) and filters the runs list accordingly."}],"totalDurationMs":20909,"totalTokens":53514,"totalToolUseCount":17,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":552,"cache_read_input_tokens":52107,"output_tokens":851,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":552},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
